observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor issue a directive to the    Municipal Accountant, the General Services Officer and the Municipal Engineer to accomplish within a definite timeline their respective tasks as enumerated in COA Circular No. 2015-008, such as:

the Municipal Engineer to provide the local Accountant and the General Services Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components of road projects;

the Municipal Accountant to keep and maintain subsidiary records     for roads and road components for every road network and disclose       in the Notes to the Financial Statements of the LGU the total road network system; and, 

the GSO maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map and keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components;

1.6	We recommended that Management direct the:
The Municipal Treasurer to prepare a schedule of unreleased/unclaimed checks at the end of the reporting period and submit thereafter to the Municipal Accountant, and;
The Municipal Accountant to post adjustment in the books of accounts that correspond to the unreleased or unclaimed checks at every end of the reporting period.

6.12.1	Ensure the timely implementation of infrastructure projects by monitoring the performance of the contractors;
Provide supporting documents in considering the suspension of work;
Re-evaluate the actual accomplishment of the contractor and consider any negative slippage incurred thereof; and
Imposed liquidated damages, if warranted, for the unperformed portion of the work for every day of delay.
